                <h1>How Far Back Does a 10 Panel Urine Test Detect Drugs?</h1>
                <p>A 10 panel urine test typically detects drug use within the past 7 to 14 days, depending on the substance and individual factors like metabolism and frequency of use. Common substances tested include THC, cocaine, opiates, and benzodiazepines. For accurate results, it's essential to consider the time frame and personal health factors.</p>
